Systemic sulfonamides are contraindicated in infants less than 2 months   of age, except in the treatment of congenital toxoplasmosis as adjunctive   therapy with pyrimethamine.
Usual Dose for Pediatric Patients Over 2 Months of Age: Initial    dose: One half of the 24-hour dose. Maintenance dose: 150 mg/kg/24 hours or    4 gm/MÂ²/24 hours - dose to be divided into 4 to 6 doses/24 hours. The maximum    dose should not exceed 6 gm/24 hours.
